-- Chile Cencosud's shares up 5.3 pct after credit card deal
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 09:39AM EDT
-- None



June 23 (Reuters) - Shares in Chilean retailer Cencosud <CEN.SN> jumped 5.3 percent at the market open on Monday, following its announcement late Friday that it would sell Bank of Nova Scotia <BNS.TO><BNS.N> a 51 percent majority stake in its retail credit card business in Chile. [ID:nL2N0P11SB]   ((anthony.esposito@thomsonreuters.com)(Twitter: @ReutersChile)(+562-2370-4253))  Keywords: CHILE STOCKS/

